During the course different options to fulfil the curriculum are introduced. An overview of different options on curriculum to specialize are given. Also the risk of burning out and loss of motivation are discussed and some hints to avoid these risks are given. Finally  different professorships of the Institute introduce the research in the chair and different ongoing projects for students to join in for specialization.
The course is linked with Faculty Career Day or Students accusation organized BioEterpreneurship Day where different companies introduce  them selves. It is obligatory to participate in these events.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course LOMR.00.105 is:  1) to introduce different options for passing the curriculum 2) to give overview of options in labour market 3) to introduce the  research in different chairs of the Institute of Molecular and Cell Biology and Institute of Genomics that is input for the further career planning. 4) to give an overview of risks during the studies (burning out, loss of motivation) and how to handle the risks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course, student: 1) has an overview of biotechnology and microbiology sector and the positions avalilable in Estonia and abroad  2) has an overview about current scientific directions and is able to choose proper field for his/her studies 3) knows projects, project coordinators and their contacts in Institute of Molecular and Cell Biology  4) is able to choose a company in which they want to know more and in which they are interested in practice
